## Enroll + provision workflow
```bash
# 1) Create node
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node create \
  --driver redfish \
  --driver-info redfish_address=<redfish https endpoint> \
  --driver-info redfish_username=<bmc user> \
  --driver-info redfish_password=<bmc password> \
  --driver-info redfish_verify_ca=False

# 2) Move to manageable
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node manage <node id>

# 3) Attach cleaning network data
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set --network-data network_data.json <node id>

# 4) Move to available (runs cleaning)
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node provide <node id>
# 5) Set deploy image (direct deploy examples)
{% if ubuntu_lts_image_enabled | bool %}
# Ubuntu whole-disk image
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info image_type=whole-disk \
  --instance-info image_disk_format={{ ubuntu_lts_image_disk_format }} \
  --instance-info image_source={{ ubuntu_lts_image_http_url }} \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_algo=sha256 \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_value=$(curl -fsSL {{ ubuntu_lts_image_checksum_http_url }})
{% else %}
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info image_type=whole-disk \
  --instance-info image_disk_format=<raw|qcow2> \
  --instance-info image_source=<url to os image> \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_algo=sha256 \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_value=<os image sha256sum>
{% endif %}
{% if flatcar_image_enabled | bool %}

# Flatcar whole-disk image
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info image_type=whole-disk \
  --instance-info image_disk_format={{ flatcar_image_disk_format }} \
  --instance-info image_source={{ flatcar_image_http_url }} \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_algo=sha256 \
  --instance-info image_os_hash_value=$(curl -fsSL {{ flatcar_image_checksum_http_url }})
{% endif %}

# 6) Deploy
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node deploy <node id> --configdrive <config-drive.json, optional>
```

## Flatcar ramdisk deployment (Ignition)
This mode boots Flatcar from kernel/initramfs in memory and does not write a persistent disk image.
Ensure your Ignition file is reachable at `{{ flatcar_ignition_http_url }}` (for example by creating `{{ flatcar_ignition_local_path }}` on the host running ironic-http).
For a quick end-to-end demo, this repository includes `server_templates/flatcar-demo.ign`, available at `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mattcburns/ironic-ansible/master/server_templates/flatcar-demo.ign`.
If you are testing from a branch/tag, replace `master` in the raw URL with that ref.
```bash
# 1) Switch node to ramdisk deploy mode
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> --deploy-interface ramdisk

# 2a) Quick demo: use this repo's sample Ignition file from GitHub raw
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info kernel={{ flatcar_ramdisk_kernel_url }} \
  --instance-info ramdisk={{ flatcar_ramdisk_initramfs_url }} \
  --instance-info ramdisk_kernel_arguments="flatcar.first_boot=1 ignition.config.url=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mattcburns/ironic-ansible/master/server_templates/flatcar-demo.ign"

# 2b) Or use your configured/local Ignition URL
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node set <node id> \
  --instance-info kernel={{ flatcar_ramdisk_kernel_url }} \
  --instance-info ramdisk={{ flatcar_ramdisk_initramfs_url }} \
  --instance-info ramdisk_kernel_arguments="{{ flatcar_ramdisk_kernel_params }}"

# 3) Deploy (boots ramdisk workload)
{{ ironic_cli_wrapper_path }} node deploy <node id>
```
The demo Ignition writes `/etc/flatcar-demo.txt` so you can validate that Ignition ran successfully.
